Sermonic Performance	KEY:Sermonic Performance ~ Evangelist	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality	BONUS:VAR|ClericChannelPositiveEnergyDice|-1|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Channel Positive Energy ~ Cleric|PRECLASS:1,Cleric=1	BONUS:VAR|ClericChannelNegativeEnergyDice|-1|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Channel Negative Energy ~ Cleric|PRECLASS:1,Cleric=1	BONUS:VAR|ClericChannelPositiveEnergyDice|-1|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Channel Positive Energy ~ Cleric|PRECLASS:1,Cleric=9	BONUS:VAR|ClericChannelNegativeEnergyDice|-1|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Channel Negative Energy ~ Cleric|PRECLASS:1,Cleric=9	BONUS:VAR|ClericChannelPositiveEnergyDice|-1|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Channel Positive Energy ~ Cleric|PRECLASS:1,Cleric=15	BONUS:VAR|ClericChannelNegativeEnergyDice|-1|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Channel Negative Energy ~ Cleric|PRECLASS:1,Cleric=15	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Bardic Performance	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Channel Energy|PRECLASS:1,Cleric=3	BONUS:VAR|BardicPerformanceLVL|classlevel("Cleric")	DESC:An evangelist gains the ability to deliver a select number of supernatural and spell-like performances through the force and power of her divinely inspired preaching and exhortation. This ability is similar in all respects to bardic performance as used by a bard of the same level (including interactions with feats, spells, and prestige classes), using Perform (oratory) as the evangelist’s performance skill. However, an evangelist gains only the following types of  bardic performance: countersong, fascinate, and inspire courage at 1st level; inspire greatness at 9th level; and inspire heroics at 15th level. Sermonic performance replaces the 1st-, 9th-, and 15th-level channel energy abilities. This caps the cleric’s channel energy damage at 7d6 points.
Spontaneous Casting	KEY:Spontaneous Casting ~ Evangelist	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality	SPELLLEVEL:CLASS|Cleric=1|Command|Cleric=2|Enthrall|Cleric=3|Tongues|Cleric=4|Suggestion|Cleric=5|Command (Greater)|Cleric=6|Geas/Quest|Cleric=7|Suggestion (Mass)|Cleric=8|Sympathy|Cleric=9|Demand	DESC:An evangelist does not gain the ability to spontaneously cast cure or inflict spells by sacrificing prepared spells. However, an evangelist can spontaneously cast command (1st), enthrall (2nd), tongues (3rd), suggestion (4th), greater command (5th), geas/quest (6th), mass suggestion (7th), sympathy (8th) and demand (9th) as a spell of listed level by sacrificing a prepared spell of the same level or higher.
